---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — Magda Kaspary" lang="en">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <div class="max-w-[68rem] mx-auto px-8 pt-16 pb-8 border-b border-stone">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-[2.8rem] font-normal leading-[1.15] text-ink">About</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-[68rem] mx-auto px-8 py-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-20 items-start">

    <main class="max-w-[42rem]">

      <div class="mb-14">
        <div class="section-label">In her own words</div>
        <p class="text-[1.2rem] leading-[1.75] text-ink">I have always believed that work can be one of the most meaningful experiences in a person's life — and that most organizations are leaving that potential almost entirely untouched. That conviction is where everything I do begins.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-14">
        <div class="section-label">The full story</div>
        <div class="bio">
          <p>My career in HR began with one clear intention: to make the workplace a more humane experience. Not more efficient. More human. That distinction has guided everything.</p>
          <p>I've had the privilege of working across many countries and cultures — <strong>from Brazil and Latin America, to leading HR for the Latin American operations of a German company, to partnering with global teams across the United States</strong>. Each cultural context taught me something no textbook could: that the way people lead, trust, communicate, and grow is shaped by invisible forces most organizations never stop to examine.</p>
          <p>What I kept discovering, in every context, was that no single discipline held the full answer. The questions that matter most — <em>Why does this team keep breaking down? What's actually blocking this leader? How do we build an environment where people genuinely bring their best?</em> — live at the intersection of psychology, systems thinking, intercultural intelligence, and coaching. I had to learn to move between those worlds. Eventually, I stopped moving between them and started inhabiting all of them at once.</p>
          <p>People often tell me I see things they couldn't quite name — a pattern in a team dynamic before it becomes a conflict, the unspoken assumption driving a decision, the emotional current running beneath a strategy conversation. That capacity came from years of <strong>deep curiosity about what moves people</strong>, and from learning to listen not just to what people say, but to what they feel and what they don't yet have words for.</p>
          <p>I am a <strong>certified coach (ICF Associate Certified Coach)</strong>, a qualified <strong>Intercultural Development Inventory administrator</strong>, and a Senior HR Business Partner at <strong>Amazon Web Services</strong>, where I partner with leaders navigating some of the most complex organizational challenges in the world.</p>
          <p>Interdisciplinarist is where all of that converges. Not a methodology. A way of seeing — and a permanent invitation to look through more than one lens.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="pull-quote">"The border between disciplines is not a wall. It's an invitation."</blockquote>

      <div class="mb-14">
        <div class="section-label">Credentials &amp; affiliations</div>
        <ul class="credentials-list">
          <li>Sr. HR Business Partner — <strong>Amazon Web Services</strong></li>
          <li>Associate Certified Coach (ACC) — <a href="https://coachingfederation.org/" target="_blank"><strong>International Coaching Federation</strong></a></li>
          <li>SHRM-SCP Senior Certified Professional — <strong>SHRM</strong></li>
          <li>SPHR — <strong>HRCI</strong></li>
          <li><a href="https://idiinventory.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Intercultural Development Inventory (IDI)</strong></a> Qualified Administrator</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.points-of-you.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Points of You®</strong></a> Practitioner</li>
          <li>Languages: Portuguese (native) · English (fluent) · Spanish (fluent)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-10">
          <div class="section-label">Publications</div>
          <ul class="credentials-list">
            <li>Book chapter author — <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Adaptive-Leadership-Economy-Routledge-Research/dp/0367567156" target="_blank"><em>Adaptive Leadership in a Global Economy</em></a> · <strong>Routledge Studies in Leadership Research</strong>, ed. Mohammed Raei &amp; Harriette Thurber Rasmussen</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    </main>

    <aside class="order-first lg:order-last lg:sticky lg:top-20">
      <img src="/images/magda-books.jpg" alt="Magda Kaspary with books" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded block" />
      <img src="/images/magda-headshot.jpg" alt="Magda Kaspary portrait" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover object-top rounded block mt-4" />
      <div class="mt-6 bg-teal-light border border-stone rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">Interested in working together or inviting Magda to speak?</p>
        <a href="/en/contact" class="block bg-teal text-white no-underline px-6 py-2.5 rounded text-[0.8rem] font-medium tracking-[0.06em] uppercase text-center hover:bg-teal-dark transition-colors">Work with Magda</a>
      </div>
    </aside>

  </div>

  <!-- NATURE BREAK -->
  <div class="nature-break">
    <img src="/images/nature-stairs.jpg" alt="" />
    <div class="nature-break-overlay"></div>
    <div class="nature-break-caption">
      <p>"I stopped moving between worlds and started inhabiting them all at once."</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-stone);
    width: 3rem;
  }

  .bio p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-bottom: 1.3rem;
  }
  .bio strong { color: var(--color-teal); font-weight: 500; }
  .bio em { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-ink-muted); }

  .pull-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 2.1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-teal);
    padding: 1rem 0 1rem 1.75rem;
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }

  .credentials-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
  }
  .credentials-list li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .credentials-list li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-teal);
  }
  .credentials-list a {
    color: var(--color-teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-stone);
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .credentials-list a:hover { border-color: var(--color-teal); }

  .nature-break {
    position: relative;
    height: 340px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .nature-break img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 35%;
    display: block;
    filter: saturate(0.78) hue-rotate(-5deg);
  }
  .nature-break-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(27,107,122,0.55) 0%, rgba(27,107,122,0.2) 60%, transparent 100%);
  }
  .nature-break-caption {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 2.5rem;
    left: 2rem;
    max-width: 36rem;
  }
  .nature-break-caption p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.4;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pull-quote { font-size: 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
